# Cursor Rules for House Project

## Project Overview
This is a React TypeScript project using:
- React 19.1.0
- TypeScript 4.9.5
- Tailwind CSS 4.1.11
- Vite 7.0.6 as the build tool
- pnpm as the package manager

## Package Manager
- Use `pnpm` for all package management operations
- Install dependencies with `pnpm install`
- Add new packages with `pnpm add <package-name>`
- Add dev dependencies with `pnpm add -D <package-name>`
- Run scripts with `pnpm <script-name>`

## Code Style & Conventions
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow React functional component patterns with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Maintain consistent file naming (PascalCase for components, camelCase for utilities)
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces

## Project Structure
- Components go in `src/components/`
- Utilities go in `src/utils/`
- Types/interfaces go in `src/types/`
- Keep components small and focused
- Use proper imports and exports

## Testing
- Use Vitest for testing
- Use React Testing Library for component testing
- Write tests for new components and utilities
- Follow testing best practices with user-centric testing

## Development Workflow
- Use `pnpm dev` for development server
- Use `pnpm build` for production builds
- Use `pnpm preview` to preview production build
- Use `pnpm test` for running tests
- Always check for TypeScript errors before committing 